# Environment Variables for Training & Utility Scripts
# 
# IMPORTANT: Streamlit app (src/ui/main.py) uses .streamlit/secrets.toml instead
# This .env is only for:
# - Training scripts (src/train.py, src/preprocess_data.py, src/label.py, etc.)
# - Utility scripts (scripts/, check_*.py, etc.)
# - Non-Streamlit environments (CI/CD, Cloud Run jobs)
#
# Copy this to .env and fill in your credentials for local development

# =============================================================================
# CLOUD SQL BACKEND (Optional - leave blank for local DuckDB)
# =============================================================================
# Required if you want to use Cloud SQL instead of local DuckDB database

# Cloud SQL instance connection string: project:region:instance-name
# Example: my-project:europe-central1:yelp-db
CLOUDSQL_INSTANCE=

# Cloud SQL user (typically "postgres")
CLOUDSQL_USER=postgres

# Cloud SQL password
CLOUDSQL_PASSWORD=

# Cloud SQL database name (typically "postgres")
CLOUDSQL_DATABASE=postgres

# =============================================================================
# GOOGLE CLOUD & AI APIs (Optional)
# =============================================================================

# Google API key for Generative AI (neuron labeling)
# Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# GitHub token for accessing GitHub Models API (neuron labeling - optional)
# Get from: https://github.com/settings/tokens
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Google Cloud Project ID (for GCS, AI services)
GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=

# Google Cloud Storage bucket name (for metadata export)
GCS_BUCKET_NAME=

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
#   - Leave all variables blank to use local DuckDB
#   - Streamlit app reads .streamlit/secrets.toml instead
#
# STREAMLIT CLOUD DEPLOYMENT:
#   - Secrets go in GitHub Secrets, NOT .env
#   - Streamlit Cloud automatically maps them to st.secrets
#   - See .streamlit/secrets.toml for format
#
# TRAINING SCRIPTS:
#   - Can read from this .env file using secrets_helper.py
#   - Set CLOUDSQL_* vars to use Cloud SQL instead of local DuckDB
#   - Set GOOGLE_API_KEY for neuron labeling
#=
